===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|ic}}: {{zh-etym-triple|木|tree}}, to suggest a large number (compare {{zh-l|*三}}) of [[trees]] such as one would find in a [[forest]]. Compare {{l|och|林}}.

===Etymology===
From {{der|zh|sit-pro|*rəm||jungle; forest; country; field}} (STEDT). {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} suggests that it may be an intensive derivation of {{l|och|林||forest}}, perhaps influenced by parallels in {{cog|aav}}, such as {{cog|okz|sarāma}}, {{m|okz|sarāṃ||a tract of stunted vegetation}}, derived from {{m|okz|rām||inundated forest along a watercourse}}. Alternatively, {{zh-ref|Mei (2012)}} suggests that the prefix ''*s-'' has a [[denominative]] function.

